Package ohos.data.resultset

Class SharedBlock

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.data.resultset.SharedBlock
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public class SharedBlock
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Stores result set data.

    This class also provides methods for operating shared blocks, such as obtaining the index of a specified column and inserting data into a specified position.

    Since:
    3
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Data#DATA_APPDATAMGR

      • getBlob

        public byte[] getBlob​(int rowIndex,
                      int columnIndex)
        Obtains the byte array value at the position specified by rowIndex and columnIndex.

        The returned result varies depending on the value type.

        • If the value type is ColumnType#TYPE_NULL, null is returned.
        • If the value type is ColumnType#TYPE_BLOB, the value is returned directly.
        • If the value type is ColumnType#TYPE_STRING, a byte array value converted from the string value is returned.
        • If the value type is ColumnType#TYPE_FLOAT or ColumnType#TYPE_INTEGER, an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        rowIndex - Indicates the specified row index, which starts from 0.
        columnIndex - Indicates the specified column index, which starts from 0.
        Returns:
        Returns the byte array value at the specified position.
        Since:
        3
